I think this will still fail for the case we looked at earlier today (where getOptionalApplication is the method that throws, but it isn't called until forEach evaluates the stream calls).
How about rewriting it to a regular loop and wrap everything except listApplications in a try-catch?
for (var application : listApplications()) {
    try {
      ...
    } catch (Exception e) {
      ...
    }
}

